brand-wizard-app/public/assets/manga_covers/ahjan_portrait.png -filter -diff -merge -text
brand-wizard-app/public/assets/manga_covers/joshin_portrait.png -filter -diff -merge -text
brand-wizard-app/public/assets/manga_covers/pamela_fellows_portrait.png -filter -diff -merge -text

# Brand-1 deep build (Layer 2 validation) — small KDP deliverables committed as
# regular git blobs, NOT LFS. Rationale: the GitHub LFS budget is exhausted (see
# teacher_pics note above), so LFS-tracked files land as 130-byte pointers with no
# real bytes pushed. These cover PNGs (<110 KB) and EPUBs (<110 KB) are all well
# under the no-binary-blobs.yml 1 MB cap, so they ship correctly as plain blobs.
artifacts/catalog/brand1_deep/**/*.png -filter -diff -merge -text
artifacts/catalog/brand1_deep/**/*.epub -filter -diff -merge -text

# Brand Director weekly deliverables (e.g. Open Vessel Press) — the rendered
# webtoon vertical strip (.png) + manga book (.pdf) the dashboard serves directly.
# Un-LFS'd for the same reason as teacher_pics above: Cloudflare Pages does not
# pull LFS, so an LFS-tracked file would serve as a 130-byte pointer and the
# image/PDF would not load. Each is < 1 MB (palette-PNG + JPEG-in-PDF), under the
# no-binary-blobs.yml cap and safe as a plain git blob.
#
# IMPORTANT — this catch-all is placed AFTER the generic *.pdf / *.png LFS rules
# above so that, for a deliveries asset, this -filter rule WINS (last match in
# .gitattributes wins). The earlier narrow `**/kdp/*.pdf` + `**/webtoon/*.png`
# rules only covered those two subdirs, so a deliveries PDF in any OTHER subdir
# still resolved to `filter: lfs` and a naive `git add` produced a broken
# ~131-byte LFS pointer instead of a plain blob. This broad pattern covers the
# whole deliveries tree.
brand-wizard-app/public/deliveries/** -filter -diff -merge -text

# Dashboard cover thumbs: small JPEGs for CF Pages (full covers stay gitignored).
brand-wizard-app/public/assets/cover_thumbs/** -filter -diff -merge -text

